After Tupac got shot at five times in the studio with Puffy and Biggie he knew he was goin' to die. So instead of makin' about one song per day, he started to make 3 songs per day, incase he would die, Death Row Records could still publish his songs and let everyone know the truth.

And yes, I know it's confusing. About 83% of the fans still hold on to the thought that Tupac is alive. Of course they think he's alive because they're his fans. I personally don't know what to think. There's many theories about his death. I don't think we will ever know the truth about his death so it's unnecessary to fight about this. Enjoy his music instead and pay attention to his lyrics.
